 web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/young-blood-single/id427517831 |title=Young Blood \u2013 Single |website=iTunes Store |location=Australia |accessdate=28 June 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/nz/album/young-blood-single/id427517831 |title=Young Blood \u2013 Single |website=iTunes Store |location=New Zealand |accessdate=28 June 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 23 February 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Digital download \u2013 Stripped\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/young-blood-stripped-single/1348233225 |title=Young Blood (Stripped) \u2013 Single by The Naked and Famous |website=iTunes Store |location=Australia |accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/nz/album/young-blood-stripped-single/1348233225 |title=Young Blood (Stripped) \u2013 Single by The Naked and Famous |website=iTunes Store |location=New Zealand |accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|the-naked-and-famous|young-blood}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{The Naked and Famous}}\n\n[[Category:APRA Award winners]]\n[[Category:2010 singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:The Naked and Famous songs]]\n[[Category:2010 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2011}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Young Blood\n| cover      = Young Blood (The Naked and Famous song) coverart.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[The Naked and Famous]]\n| album      = [[Passive Me, Aggressive You]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2010|6|7|df=yes}}\n| format     =\n* [[CD single|CD]]\n* [[7-inch single|7-inch]]\n* [[Music download|digital download]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     = The Lab, [[Auckland]], New Zealand\n| genre      = [[Synth-pop]]\n| length     = 3:53\n| label      = Somewhat Damaged\n| writer     =\n* Thom Powers\n* Alisa Xayalith\n* Aaron Short\n| producer   =\n* Thom Powers\n* Aaron Short\n| prev_title = All of This\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[Punching in a Dream]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = Alternative cover\n | type    = single\n | cover   = The_Naked_and_Famous_Young_Blood_UK.jpg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = UK and US cover\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Young Blood'''\" is a song by New Zealand band [[The Naked and Famous]] from their debut studio album, ''[[Passive Me, Aggressive You]]'' (2010). It was released on 7 July 2010 as the album's second single. \"Young Blood\" debuted at number one on the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]]. The song received the 2010 [[APRA Awards (New Zealand)|Silver Scroll]] for Song of the Year.\n\n==Composition==\n\"Young Blood\" is a [[synth-pop]] song,<ref name=\"BBCmusic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/dnfd |title=The Naked and Famous Passive Me, Aggressive You Review |first=Kevin |last=Harley |publisher=[[BBC Music]] |date=3 March 2011 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> featuring a buzz-guitar riff.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/the-naked-and-famous/11895 |title=Album Review: The Naked and Famous \u2013 Passive Me, Aggressive You (Fiction) |first=Mark |last=Beaumont |work=[[NME]] |date=9 March 2011 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> Kevin Harley of [[BBC Music]] compared the song to the work of [[MGMT]].<ref name=\"BBCmusic\"/> According to Godfrey de Grut of ''NZ Musician'', \"Young Blood\" is set in the [[key (music)|key]] of [[F-sharp major|F#]], and follows the [[chord progression]] of B\u2013F{{music|sharp}}\u2013B\u2013F{{music|sharp}}\u2013C{{music|sharp}}\u2013B\u2013F{{music|sharp}}\u2013B\u2013D{{music|sharp}}min\u2013C{{music|sharp}}.<ref name=\"NZM\">{{cite journal |issn=0114-9032 |first=Godfrey |last=de Grut |magazine=NZ Musician |url=http://www.nzmusician.co.nz/index.php/ps_pagename/article/pi_articleid/2133 |title=X Factory: The Naked and Famous \u2013 Young Blood |date=October\u2013November 2010 |volume=15 |issue=9}}</ref> The theme of \"Young Blood\" is that of \"spirit of youth\" and its loss,<ref name=\"NZM\"/><ref>{{cite news |title=CD Reviews |first=Nick |last=Ward |newspaper=[[The Nelson Mail]] |date=23 September 2010 |page=12}}</ref> and contains a \"yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah\" [[Hook (music)|hook]].<ref name=\"NZM\"/><ref name=\"NZHreview\"/>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe song received critical acclaim by music critics. [[AllMusic]]'s Matt Collar noted \"Young Blood\" as one of the top tracks from ''Passive Me, Aggressive You'' and described it as \"layered and shimmering\".<ref name=\"Allreview\">{{Allmusic|id=r2130958 |class=album |tab=review |first=Matt |last=Collar |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> Tom Cardy from ''[[The Dominion Post (Wellington)|The Dominion Post]]'' called it \"one of the catchiest indie electro tunes I've heard in years\".<ref name=\"TDP\">{{cite web |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/dominion-post/culture/film-reviews/4135069/CD-Review-The-Naked-and-Famous-Passive-Me-Aggressive-You |title=CD Review The Naked and Famous \u2013 Passive Me Aggressive You |first=Tom |last=Cardy |work=[[The Dominion Post (Wellington)|The Dominion Post]] |date=16 September 2010 |accessdate=15 November 2019}}</ref> ''[[The New Zealand Herald]]''{{'s}} Scott Kara labelled \"Young Blood\" as \"an inventive, rousing, and uplifting tune\".<ref name=\"NZHreview\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=10672032 |title=Album Review: The Naked and Famous ''Passive Me, Aggressive You'' |first=Scott |last=Kara |work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |date=9 September 2010 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 September 2010 \"Young Blood\" won the [[APRA Awards (New Zealand)|APRA Silver Scroll]], a New Zealand peer-judged songwriting award. APRA's Anthony Healey stated, \"Young Blood is outstanding; it's stroppy, it's youthful and energetic. It makes me want to be eighteen again\".<ref name=\"Sundae\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=10671929 |title=The Naked and Famous win APRA Silver Scroll |first=Hugh |last=Sundae |date=8 September 2010 |work=The New Zealand Herald |publisher=APN News & Media |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> At the awards ceremony it was covered by [[reggae]] band Three Houses Down.<ref name=\"Sundae\"/> The Naked and Famous said being awarded with the honour was \"surreal and intense\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/music/4109530/Young-Blood-wins-Silver-Scroll |title=Young Blood wins Silver Scroll |first1=Bridget |last1=Jones |first2=Victoria |last2=Robinson |publisher=[[Stuff (website)|Stuff]]. Fairfax New Zealand |date=9 September 2010 |archiveurl=\nhttps://www.webcitation.org/5y2yDuGDL?url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/music/4109530/Young-Blood-wins-Silver-Scroll |archivedate=18 April 2011 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Young Blood\" debuted atop the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]] on 14 June 2010,<ref name=\"NZ\"/> becoming the first time a New Zealand artist debuted at number one in over three years;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvnz.co.nz/entertainment-news/silver-scroll-winner-announced-3767270 |title=Silver Scroll winner announced |author=[[One News (New Zealand)|One News]] |publisher=[[TVNZ]] |date=8 September 2010 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> [[Matthew Saunoa]]'s \"[[Hold Out (song)|Hold Out]]\" did so in November 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rianz.org.nz/rianz/chart.asp?chartNum=1537&chartKind=S |title=Top 40 singles (#1537) |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand]] |date=6 November 2006 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> The song held the top spot for another week, however on 28 June it was pushed to number two by \"[[California Gurls]]\" by [[Katy Perry]] and [[Snoop Dogg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rianz.org.nz/rianz/chart.asp?chartNum=1727&chartKind=S |title=Top 40 singles (#1727) |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand]] |date=28 June 2010 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> \"Young Blood\" fell out of the singles chart in October 2010, having spent 18 weeks on the chart.<ref name=\"NZ\"/>\n\nIn Australia, \"Young Blood\" peaked at number 26 on the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Singles Chart]], while in Austria it remained on the [[\u00d63 Austria Top 40]] for 10 weeks, reaching number 53. The song peaked at number 59 on the Dutch [[Single Top 100]] chart, spending five weeks on the chart.<ref name=\"NZ\"/>\n\nIn the United States, the song was featured as [[iTunes Store]] Single of the Week and was available for free of charge download during the week of 15\u201321 March 2011. It was certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) on 10 December 2013, denoting sales in excess of one million copies.<ref name=\"RIAA\"/>\n\n==Music video==\nThe accompanying music video for \"Young Blood\" was directed by Joel Kefali and Campbell Hooper of Special Problems.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenakedandfamous.com/?c=-1 |title=The Naked + Famous |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5y2w2bqJN?url=http://www.thenakedandfamous.com/?c=-1 |archivedate=18 April 2011 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Covers and use in media==\n[[Jessie J]] covered \"Young Blood\" for [[BBC Radio 1]]'s [[Live Lounge]] in March 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artistdirect.com/entertainment-news/article/jessie-j-covers-the-naked-and-famous-young-blood-for-bbc-radio-1/8718787 |title=Jessie J Covers The Naked and Famous' 'Young Blood' For BBC Radio 1 |publisher=[[Artistdirect]] |date=7 March 2011 |accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> [[Chiddy Bang]] remixed it in September 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Like A Version: Chiddy Bang \u2013 Young Blood|url=http://www.abc.net.au/triplej/tomandalex/blog/s3026975.htm|work=Triple J|accessdate=17 September 2011|author=Tom and Alex|date=17 September 2011}}</ref> [[Birdy (musician)|Birdy]] covered the song on her eponymous debut album ''[[Birdy (Birdy album)|Birdy]]''. Her version was featured in the \"[[Grey's Anatomy (season 8)#Episodes|Moment of Truth]]\" episode of ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' and on ''[[Harry's Law]]'' at the end of episode \"The Contest\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Grey's Anatomy \"Moment of Truth Music|url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/music/shows/greys-anatomy/episodes/moment-of-truth.html|work=TV Fanatic|accessdate=14 May 2012}}</ref> A remix was also made by Dutch DJs [[Ti\u00ebsto]] and [[Hardwell]], whose version appears on Ti\u00ebsto's album ''[[Club Life: Volume Two Miami]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tiesto's Club Life \u2013 Volume Two Miami A Tribute To City He Loves|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1683811/tiesto-club-life-miami-tribute.jhtml|publisher=MTV|accessdate=13 May 2012|author=Akshay Bhansali|date=24 April 2012}}</ref> [[Machine Gun Kelly (rapper)|Machine Gun Kelly]] sampled \"Young Blood\" in his \"[[Half Naked & Almost Famous]]\" single.\n\nIn August 2010, the Israeli clothing company [[Castro (clothing)|Castro]] featured \"Young Blood\" in their shoes commercial and later, on November 2010 the Winter collection advertisement included acoustic cover of the song. In March 2011, Castro used it again in their shoes commercial. With the relaunch of the television channel [[Viva (TV station)|Viva]] on 1 January 2011, \"Young Blood\" gained popularity in Germany and Austria as it is used in the channels' idents and trailers. The song was featured in the [[Strongbow (cider)|Strongbow]] 'Summer Blossom' advert in Australia. In Uzbekistan, the song was used in the advertisement of the mobile network operator UCell during May and June 2011. It was also used in [[Canon (company)|Canon]] camera adverts. It was used as the theme of the French television series ''[[:fr:La Nouvelle \u00c9dition|La Nouvelle \u00c9dition]]'' (2011\u20132013). This song was played right before the unveiling of the all-new 2013 [[Nissan Altima]] at the 2012 [[New York International Auto Show]].{{citation needed|date=April 2012}}\n\n[[Ultimate Fighting Championship|UFC]] [[Mixed martial arts|MMA]] fighter [[Maur\u00edcio Rua|Maur\u00edcio \"Shogun\" Rua]] used it as walk in music at [[UFC on Fox 4]]. \"Young Blood\" was featured in the Disney film ''[[Prom (film)|Prom]]'' and in its trailer. The song was featured in the pilot of ''[[Covert Affairs]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Covert Affairs Episode Music Guide|url=http://www.usanetwork.com/series/covertaffairs/theshow/blogs/musiclist.html|publisher=USA Network|accessdate=15 September 2011}}</ref> in both the first and last episodes of ''[[The Almighty Johnsons]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=The Almighty Johnsons \u2013 Music|url=http://thealmightyjohnsons.co.nz/music/|accessdate=15 September 2011}}</ref> and in the [[Chuck Versus the Push Mix|thirteenth episode]] of the [[Chuck (season 4)|fourth season]] of [[NBC]]'s ''[[Chuck (TV series)|Chuck]]'', during a sequence which was called the \"best 10&nbsp;minutes in the show's history\" by series creator [[Josh Schwartz]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Sepinwall |first=Alan |url=http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/whats-alan-watching/posts/chuck-chuck-vs-the-gobbler-the-undercover-lover |title=Chuck \u2013 Chuck vs. the Gobbler: The undercover lover |publisher=HitFix.com |date=2012-03-12 |accessdate=2012-03-16}}</ref> The song was further featured in the episode \"Panic Roommate\" of the fourth season of ''[[Gossip Girl (TV series)|Gossip Girl]]'',<ref>[http://www.cwtv.com/music/gossip-girl/thenakedandfamous The Naked And Famous artist spotlight on CW Music page, \"Gossip Girl\" section.]</ref><ref>[http://www.tvfanatic.com/2011/02/gossip-girl-music-from-panic-roommate/ TV Fanatic.com \"Panic Roommate\" episode music guide.]</ref> in the season 3 premiere of TVNZ's ''[[Go Girls]]'',<ref>[http://www.tvnz.co.nz/Go-Girls]</ref> and in a promo for the British show ''[[Skins (TV series)|Skins]]''. \"Young Blood\" was then used in the third episode of [[MTV]]'s TV series ''[[Awkward (TV series)|Awkward]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Awkward. \" Songs From the Show \" Ep. 103 |url=http://www.mtv.com/shows/awkward/episode_music.jhtml?episodeID=182129|publisher=MTV|accessdate=17 September 2011|date=2 August 2011}}</ref> and in the pilot of ''[[The Secret Circle (TV series)|The Secret Circle]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Secret Circle \u2013 Pilot|url=https://www.tunefind.com/show/the-secret-circle/season-1/9556|publisher=Tunefind|accessdate=September 12, 2018}}</ref> It is featured on the season finale of ''[[Whitney (TV series)|Whitney]]''. The song was featured in Travis Rice's ''[[The Art of Flight]]'', a snowboarding film released 7 September 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Art of Flight Soundtrack|url=http://www.redbullusa.com/cs/Satellite/en_US/Article/art-of-flight-soundtrack-021243086400429|publisher=redbullusa.com|accessdate=4 May 2012|date=16 September 2011}}</ref> A promo for the second season of the [[HGTV]] show ''[[Property Brothers]]'' features a cut of the song. The song is featured on the FOX telecast of the 2011 Major League Baseball World Series. The song is also featured in the trailer for the movies ''[[The Cabin in the Woods]]'' and ''[[Prom (film)|Prom]]''. The song was featured a bit in the Season 11 premiere of ''[[American Idol]]''. The song is featured on the soundtrack for video game ''[[SSX (2012 video game)|SSX]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=SSX Soundtrack To Feature Foster The People, Pretty Lights, The Naked And Famous And Many More|url=http://www.ea.com/uk/news/ssx-soundtrack-has-46-songs-from-artists|work=EA News|publisher=ea.com|accessdate=14 May 2012|date=7 February 2012}}</ref> An alternate version of the song with a slower tempo is currently being featured in commercials for Trident Gum. This version is known as the Renholder Remix and was used in the soundtrack for ''[[Underworld: Awakening]]''. A remix of the song by Dekade was featured in the 2013 American comedy film ''[[21 & Over (film)|21 & Over]]''. In the Philippines, meanwhile, the song is used as the opening theme song of ''#SU'', a student-oriented magazine TV talk show produced by students of [[Silliman University]] in [[Dumaguete City]]. The show airs weekly on local cable TV station Fil Products Channel 6.\n\nThis song was also used during the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] 2011-2012 television schedule promo. It was featured in episode 10 of ''[[Germany's Next Topmodel, Cycle 6]]'' and in the 2013 films ''[[Carrie (2013 film)|Carrie]]'' and ''[[21 & Over (film)|21 & Over]]''.\n\n==Track listings==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n*'''Digital download'''\n# \"Young Blood\" \u2013 3:52\n\n*'''German CD single and UK 7-inch vinyl 1'''<ref name=\"GERcd\"/><ref name=\"7inch1\"/>\n# \"Young Blood\" \u2013 3:53\n# \"[[Crazy? Yes! Dumb? No!]]\" \u2013 6:30\n\n*'''UK CD single'''\n# \"Young Blood\" (Radio Edit) \u2013 3:35\n# \"Young Blood\" \u2013 3:53\n\n*'''UK 7-inch vinyl 2'''<ref name=\"7inch2\"/>\n# \"Young Blood\" \u2013 3:53\n# \"Sow\" \u2013 4:10\n\n{{col-2}}\n*'''New Zealand and Australian digital download 2'''\n# \"Young Blood\" (Radio Edit) \u2013 3:34\n# \"Young Blood\" (Chiddy Bang Remix) \u2013 3:32\n\n*'''UK and Irish digital EP'''<ref name=\"EP\"/>\n# \"Young Blood\" \u2013 3:54\n# \"Sow\" \u2013 4:06\n# \"Young Blood\" (David Andrew Sitek Remix) \u2013 3:36\n# \"Young Blood\" (Music video) \u2013 3:57\n\n*'''Digital remix single'''\n# \"Young Blood\" ([[Ti\u00ebsto]] & [[Hardwell]] Remix Radio Edit) \u2013 3:31\n# \"Young Blood\" (Ti\u00ebsto & Hardwell Remix) \u2013 6:37\n\n*'''Digital download \u2013 Stripped'''\n# \"Young Blood\" (Stripped) \u2013 3:49\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2010\u201312)\n! scope=\