{"title_page": "Perth Glory FC (W-League)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Perth Glory FC W-League\n| image = Perth Glory FC W-League logo.png\n| caption = \n| fullname = Perth Glory Women's Football Club\n| nickname = The Glory Girls\n| short name = PGFC\n| founded = {{start date and age|2008}}\n| ground = [[Dorrien Gardens]] ([[West Perth, Western Australia|West Perth]])<br>[[Perth Oval|HBF Park]] ([[Perth]])\n| capacity = 4,000<br>20,500\n| chrtitle  = Chairman\n|  chairman = [[Tony Sage]]\n| mgrtitle   = Head Coach\n| manager    = [[Bobby Despotovski]]\n| league     = {{Australian soccer updater-W|PerthG}}\n| season     = {{Australian soccer updater-W|PerthG2}}\n| position   = {{Australian soccer updater-W|PerthG3}}\n| current    = 2018\u201319 Perth Glory W-League season\n| website = http://www.perthglory.com.au/\n|pattern_la1 = _glory1718h\n|pattern_la2 = _glory1718a\n|pattern_b1  = _glory1718h\n|pattern_b2  = _glory1718a\n|pattern_ra1 = _glory1718h\n|pattern_ra2 = _glory1718a\n|pattern_sh1 = _glory1718h\n|pattern_sh2 = _glory1718a\n|pattern_so1 = _glory1718h\n|pattern_so2 = _glory1718a\n|leftarm1    = 5A0192\n|leftarm2    = 5A0192\n|body1       = 5A0192\n|body2       = 5A0192\n|rightarm1   = 5A0192\n|rightarm2   = 5A0192\n|shorts1     = 5A0192\n|shorts2     = FFFFFF\n|socks1      = 4A0673\n|socks2      = FFFFFF\n}}\n\n{{sidebar\n| titlestyle = font-size: 125%; background-color: #5C2482; color: #FFFFFF\n| title = Active departments of<br>Perth Glory\n| contentstyle = padding-top:0.5em;\n| content1 = {{aligned table|cols=3|fullwidth=y\n\n| [[Image:Football pictogram.svg|30px]]\n| [[Image:Football pictogram.svg|30px]]\n| [[Image:Football pictogram.svg|30px]]\n| [[Perth Glory FC|Football<br>(Men's)]]\n| [[Perth Glory FC Youth and Under-23s|Football<br>(Youth Men's)]]\n| Football<br>(Women's)\n}}}}\n\nThe '''Perth Glory FC''', also known as the '''Perth Glory Women''', represents the [[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]] in the [[W-League (Australia)|W-League]], the top division women's football (soccer) league in Australia. The team was established in 2008, with the founding of the new league.<ref name=\"equalizer_112613\">{{cite web|last1=Grainey|first1=Tim|title=Grainey: A closer look at the Westfield W-League|url=http://equalizersoccer.com/2013/11/26/australia-westfield-w-league-heats-up/|work=The Equalizer |accessdate=2 October 2016|date=November 26, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Perth Glory FC|url=http://au.women.soccerway.com/teams/australia/perth-glory/12643/|website=Soccerway|accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref> They use [[Dorrien Gardens]] as their main home grounds since the [[2017\u201318 W-League|2017\u201318 Season]].\n\n==History==\n===Establishment===\n{{see also|W-League (Australia)#History}}\nAfter [[Australia women's national soccer team|Australia]] reached the quarter-finals of the [[2007 FIFA Women's World Cup]] for the first time, head coach [[Tom Sermanni]] felt the establishment of a professional league was vital for continuing the development of players.<ref>{{cite web|last=Grainey|first=Tim|title=Grainey: A closer look at the Westfield W-League|url=http://equalizersoccer.com/2013/11/26/australia-westfield-w-league-heats-up/|work=The Equalizer|accessdate=14 December 2013|date=26 November 2013}}</ref> Perth Glory was one of eight teams included in the establishment of the league the following year by [[Football Federation Australia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.footballaustralia.com.au/InsideFFA/default.aspx?s=insideffa_newsfeatures_newsitem&id=22966|title=Women in a league of their own|date=28 July 2008|publisher=[[Football Federation Australia]]}}</ref>\n\n==Ownership and team management==\n{{see also|Perth Glory FC#Ownership_and_finances}}\nPerth Glory is owned by [[Tony Sage]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Perth Glory owner Tony Sage says club does not have culture of systemic salary cap rorting|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-04-17/glory-does-not-have-rorting-culture-tony-sage/6402670|work=ABC News|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=2 October 2016|date=17 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nDuring the team's inaugural season, the women's team was managed by [[Nicola Williams]] who improved to be a top\u2013four performing side in the second half of the season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nicola Williams named as Glory W-League coach|url=http://www.w-league.com.au/article/nicola-williams-named-as-glory-w-league-coach/1iqmie8pyi3f612flvc492g09l|publisher=W-League|accessdate=2 October 2016|date=5 September 2008}}</ref><ref>[http://www.perthglory.com.au/default.aspx?s=newsdisplay&id=27162 Oxtoby the most Glorious]</ref> In 2010, [[Jamie Harnwell]] was named head coach and led the team to second and first place finishes and a first-time trip to the finals.<ref>{{cite web|title=Harnwell's heyday isn't over|url=http://www.socceroos.com.au/article/harnwells-heyday-isnt-over/1gie6voinpyfs16wx8rdy7sa75|publisher=Socceroos|accessdate=2 October 2016|date=12 December 2012}}</ref> In July 2015, former A-League striker [[Bobby Despotovski]] was named head coach with former Matilda and Perth Glory captain [[Collette McCallum]] as assistant coach.<ref>{{cite web|title=Glory stalwart appointed to lead W-League outfit|url=http://www.footballaustralia.com.au/article/bobby-despotovski-appointed-as-perth-glorys-w-league-coach/1w0tpwerv5o6b1oisaiigiyjal|publisher=Football Federation Australia|accessdate=2 October 2016|date=22 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Players==\n{{see also|List of Perth Glory FC W-League players}}\n\n===Current squad===\nUpdated 13 November 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.perthglory.com.au/news/new-westfield-w-league-squad-taking-shape|title=New Westfield W-League squad taking shape|publisher=[[Perth Glory FC]]|author=Gareth Morgan|accessdate=18 October 2019|date=18 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"perth\">{{cite news |title=REIGN FC\u2019S ANDREWS, JIM\u00c9NEZ DELGADO JOIN PERTH GLORY FC FOR W-LEAGUE SEASON