81423.html|work=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]|agency=[[Press Trust of India]] |date=28 April 2018 |location=New Delhi}}</ref>\n****[[Python-5]] (future)<ref name=\"vayu-sepoct14\">{{cite magazine|last=Majumdar|first=Sayan |title=Tejas Redux: The Israeli Touch|magazine=Vayu Aerospace and Defence Review |date=September\u2013October 2014|issue=5|pages=82\u201384|publisher=Society for Aerospace Studies}}</ref>\n****[[R-73 (missile)|R-73]]<ref name=\"awst-11apr11\"/>\n****[[R-77]]\n****[[ASRAAM]] (expected)<ref>{{cite news |title=India moves towards broad adoption of ASRAAM |url=https://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/india-moves-towards-broad-adoption-of-asraam-460441/|accessdate=7 September 2019|newspaper=FlightGlobal |date=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n****[[Meteor (missile)|Meteor]] (future)\n*** [[Air-to-surface missile]]\n****BrahMos-NG [[Air-launched cruise missile|ALCM]] (planned for Tejas Mk.1A)<ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite news |title=India likely to induct air-launched BrahMos-A by early 2020 |url=https://www.janes.com/article/86816/india-likely-to-induct-air-launched-brahmos-a-by-early-2020|accessdate=7 September 2019|newspaper=Jane's 360 |date=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n****[[Kh-59|Kh-59ME]], [[Kh-59|Kh-59L]], [[Kh-59|Kh-59T]]<ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n*** [[Anti-radiation missile]]\n****[[Kh-31|Kh-31P]]\n****[[DRDO Anti-Radiation Missile|NGARM]] (future)<ref name=\"the hindu\">{{cite news |title=Captive flight trials of anti-radiation missile soon |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/captive-flight-trials-of-antiradiation-missile-soon/article8245955.ece |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |publisher=[[The Hindu Group]] |date=17 February 2016 |accessdate=18 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160220141757/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/captive-flight-trials-of-antiradiation-missile-soon/article8245955.ece |archivedate=20 February 2016}}</ref>\n*** [[Anti-ship missile]]\n****[[Kh-35]]\n****[[Kh-59|Kh-59MK]]\n****[[Brahmos]] (planned for Tejas naval variant)<ref name=\"auto7\"/>\n|hardpoint bombs=<br/> (supports [[Constantly computed impact point|CCRP]]/[[Constantly computed impact point|CCIP]] mode)\n*** [[Unguided bombs]]\n*** [[Sudarshan laser-guided bomb]]<ref name=\"flight-15nov16\">{{cite magazine |title=HAL to hike Tejas output as India approves order|magazine=[[Flight International]] |date=15\u201321 November 2016|issue=5563|volume=190|page=20 |location=London|publisher=[[Reed Business Information]] |issn=0015-3710}}</ref>\n*** [[Spice (bomb)|Spice]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Indian Air Force Plans Israeli Spice Smart Bombs for HAL Tejas |url=https://eurasiantimes.com/iaf-tejas-fighters-testing-advanced-israeli-missiles-and-bombs-israeli-media/ |website=The EurAsian Times |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*** [[High Speed Low Drag Bomb]]\n*** [[DRDO Smart Anti-Airfield Weapon]]\n*** [[DRDO Glide Bombs]]<ref name=\"flight-15nov16\"/>\n*** [[Cluster bombs]] (expected)<ref name=\"awst-11apr11\"/>\n|hardpoint other=<br />\n*** [[Aerial refuelling]] probe compatible with [[NATO]] and Russian tankers\n*** [[Drop tank]]s for ferry flight/extended range/loitering time\n*** [[LITENING]] GR4 targeting pod<ref name=\"vayu-sepoct14\"/>\n|avionics=* Hybrid Elta [[EL/M-2032|EL/M-2032]] multi-mode all weather [[fire control radar]] with day and night capability.<ref name=\"Defence Aviation\">{{cite news |title=LCA Tejas finally gets Radar! |url=http://www.defenceaviation.com/2010/04/lca-tejas-finally-gets-radar.html |publisher=Defence Aviation |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=1 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160405024001/http://www.defenceaviation.com/2010/04/lca-tejas-finally-gets-radar.html |archivedate=5 April 2016}}</ref> [[EL/M-2052]] [[Active electronically scanned array|AESA]] radar with EL/L-8222 [[Electronic countermeasure|ECM]] pod for Mk.1A.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pubby |first1=Manu |title=Israeli super radars set to give desi LCA fighter jet enhanced combat capability |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/israeli-super-radars-set-to-give-desi-lca-fighter-jet-enhanced-combat-capability/articleshow/64111919.cms |accessdate=2 March 2020 |agency=ET Bureau |publisher=The Economic Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Franz |first1=Stefan Gady |title=India Selects Israeli Radar and Electronic Warfare Suite For Tejas Light Combat Aircraft |url=https://thediplomat.com/2018/12/india-selects-israeli-radar-and-electronic-warfare-suite-for-tejas-light-combat-aircraft/ |accessdate=2 March 2020 |agency=Diplomat Media Inc. |publisher=The Diplomat}}</ref> \n*Mayavi [[electronic warfare]] (EW) suite with [[radar warning receiver]] (RWR), [[Missile Approach Warning|missile approach warning]] (MAW), [[Laser warning receiver|laser warning receiver]] (LWR) and [[electronic countermeasure]] (ECM) system\n* Full authority quadruplex [[fly-by-wire]] fail-operational/[[fail-safe]] digital automatic flight control system (DAFCS) with stability/command augmentation, carefree manoeuvring, [[Autopilot|autopilot control]] and [[ski-jump]] function. Advanced flight control actuators with dual redundant hydraulic and quad redundant electrical power supply. \n* [[Fibre-optic gyroscope|Fibre-optic gyro]] based [[inertial navigation system]] integrated with [[Galileo (satellite navigation)|Galileo]]/[[GPS]]/[[GLONASS]]/[[NavIC]] [[satellite guidance]] and [[tactical air navigation]] (TACAN) system \n* [[VHF]]/[[UHF]] [[radio communication]] with in-built counter-countermeasure system, supports air-to-air and air-to-ground via secure [[datalink]]\n* Digital weapon management system (DWMS), compatible with NATO and Russian standards \n* [[MIL-STD-1553B]] [[32-bit]] [[dual modular redundancy]] [[open architecture]] mission computer \n* [[Infrared search and track]] (IRST) system and [[laser designator]] / [[rangefinder]]\n* [[Ground proximity warning system|Ground proximity warning]] and [[TERPROM|terrain referenced navigation system]] \n* [[VHF omnidirectional range]]\u2013[[instrument landing system]] (VOR\u2013ILS)\n* Computer controlled utility system and management system (USMS)\n* [[Air data computer|Air data system]] (ADS) with fail-operational/[[fail-safe]] modes\n* [[Ultraviolet]] and [[infrared]] missile warning sensors, self-protection jammer \n* [[Health and usage monitoring systems]] (HUMS)\n* [[MIL-STD-1760|MIL-STD-1760C]] stores management system \n* ''Get you home'' pilot help emergency system with automatic landing system \n* Environment monitoring system\n* [[Identification friend or foe]] (IFF) \n* [[Chaff (countermeasure)|Chaff]], [[Chaff (countermeasure)|jaff]] and [[flares]] dispenser \n* Towed radar decoy (TRD)\n; Cockpit:\n* [[Elbit]]-furnished DASH [[helmet-mounted display]] and sight (HMDS)\n* On board oxygen generation system (OBOGS)<ref>{{cite web |title=Rajnath\u2019s LCA sortie: Why Onboard Oxygen Generating System is a boon for pilots |url=https://www.mynation.com/india-news/rajnath-s-lca-sortie-why-onboard-oxygen-generating-system-is-a-boon-for-pilots-py2klx |website=My Nation |publisher=Asianet News Group |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> \n* Night-vision goggles compatible [[glass cockpit]]\n* [[Hands-on-throttle-and-stick]] (HOTAS) controls\n\n}}\n\n==See also==\n{{aircontent\n|see also=\n* [[HAL Tejas timeline]]\n|related=\n* [[HAL Tejas Mk2]]\n<!-- Comparable/similar aircraft section removed because of edit wars - see talk page. DISCUSS on talk page and get a consensus to restore list. -->\n|lists=<!-- relevant lists that this aircraft appears in: -->\n* [[List of fighter aircraft]]\n* [[List of active Indian military aircraft]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist|group=N}}\n\n===Citations===\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{citation |editor1-last=Jackson |editor1-first=Paul |editor2-last=Munson |editor2-first=Kenneth |editor3-last=Peacock |editor3-first=Lindsay |title=Jane's All The World's A