{"title_page": "KIYU", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox Radio station\n | name             = KIYU\n | image            = KIYU-AMandFM 2016.PNG\n | image_size       = 150px\n | city             = [[Galena, Alaska]]\n | area             = [[Alaska Bush]]\n | branding         = KIYU\n | slogan           = ''\"Community Radio for Alaska\"''\n | airdate          = July 4, 1986<ref name=\"LaunchDate\"/>\n | frequency        = {{Frequency|[[910 AM]]|[[kHz]]}}\n | format           = [[Public Radio]]<ref name=\"Arbitron\"/>\n | power            = 5,000 [[Watt]]s daytime<br>1,000 [[Watt]]s nighttime\n | class            = B\n | facility_id      = 5282\n | coordinates      = {{coord|64|41|18|N|156|43|29|W|type:landmark}}\n | callsign_meaning =\n | former_callsigns =\n | owner            = Big River Public Broadcasting Corporation\n | licensee         =\n | sister_stations  =\n | webcast          = [http://104.171.100.15:8001/xstream.m3u KIYU Webstream]\n | website          = [http://www.kiyu.com/ KIYU Online]\n | affiliations     = [[Alaska Public Media|Alaska Public Radio Network]]<br>[[National Public Radio]]\n}}\n\n'''KIYU''' is a [[Public Radio]] formatted [[Broadcasting|broadcast]] [[radio station]] licensed to [[Galena, Alaska]], serving the [[Alaska Bush]].<ref name=\"Arbitron\"/>  KIYU is owned and operated by Big River Public Broadcasting Corporation.<ref name=\"FCC\"/>\n\n==Rebroadcasters==\nIn addition to the main station, KIYU is relayed on 11 full-power FM repeaters to widen its broadcast area. KIYU programming is also simulcast on [[KRFF (FM)|KRFF]] in Fairbanks, weekdays from 1:00pm to 4:00pm.<ref name=\"KRFF\"/>\n{{RadioTranslators\n| call1    = KALG\n| freq1    = 98.1\n| fid1     = 178864\n| watts1   = 100 [[Watt]]s\n| haat1    = -77\n| class1   = D\n| city1    = Kaltag, Alaska\n| coord1   = {{coord|64|19|40|N|158|43|36|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes1   = <ref name=\"KALG\"/>\n| call2    = KAMN\n| freq2    = 98.1\n| fid2     = 180624\n| wa